Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setPinDensityMapMode(25.10)                        setPinDensityMapMode(25.10)

Name
       setPinDensityMapMode  -  Sets global parameters for the reportPinDensi-
       tyMap command

Syntax
       setPinDensityMapMode

       [-help]

       [-reset]

       [-displayStep <step_value>]

       [-gridInMicron <micron>]

       [-gridInRow <numberRow>]

       [-threshold <density>]

       Sets global parameters for the reportPinDensityMap command.  Parameters
       that  you  specify with setPinDensityMapMode are then used when you run
       reportPinDensityMap.

       Parameters specified by the reportPinDensityMap command  supersede  the
       parameters specified by the setPinDensityMapMode command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each setPinDensityMapMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setPinDensityMapMode

       -reset Resets all or specified options to default value.

              Any values that do not already match the default value  and  are
              reset will be reported.

       -displayStep <step_value>
              Specifies the range step for displaying the pin density map cal-
              culations.

              Default: .05

       -gridInMicron <micron>
              Specifies  the  value (in micron) of side of the square grid for
              pin density calculations.

              Default: 50

              Minimum: 0.000000

              Maximum: 1000.000000

       -gridInRow <numberRow>
              Specifies the value (in row-height) of side of the  square  grid
              for pin density calculations.

              Default: 10

              Minimum: 1

              Maximum: 100

       -threshold <density>
              Specifies  the  threshold value over which the densities must be
              reported.

              Default: 0.5

Related Information
              * getPinDensityMapMode

              * reportPinDensityMap

